WEBVTT

00:24.232 --> 00:27.234
settle down, everybody. Quiet, please.

00:28.319 --> 00:31.447
Mobile phones off, thank you very much.

00:33.575 --> 00:34.366
Okay.

00:36.578 --> 00:39.621
so what is it that makes us what we are?

00:41.416 --> 00:43.542
What is it that defines us?

00:45.670 --> 00:47.212
Is it where we live?

00:48.757 --> 00:50.340
Is it our schooling?

00:52.093 --> 00:53.635
Or is it our family?

00:55.930 --> 00:57.890
Alex Rider. Family?

01:00.769 --> 01:01.894
Alex?

01:04.647 --> 01:05.606
Yes, sir?

01:06.524 --> 01:08.067
Have you prepared something for us?

01:10.528 --> 01:11.236
Yes.

01:12.280 --> 01:13.072
Come on then.

01:25.668 --> 01:27.586
There's not much
I can say about my family.

01:28.671 --> 01:31.381
I didn't know my parents,
they died when I was small.

01:33.134 --> 01:34.259
I live with my uncle.

01:37.263 --> 01:39.640
He's never around so I can't tell you
much about him either.

01:39.849 --> 01:42.643
I have a housekeeper
because he's always away on business.

01:42.977 --> 01:45.145
she's an American and
her name is Jack.

01:45.730 --> 01:48.148
she's always there for me,
which is great because...

01:48.608 --> 01:49.775
he isn't.

01:50.652 --> 01:51.485
My uncle...

01:52.695 --> 01:55.864
he's never gonna set the world on fire
because he's got a real boring Job.

02:02.330 --> 02:03.497
Intruder alert!

02:05.667 --> 02:09.669
His work means a lot to him,
but, he never talks about it.

02:18.471 --> 02:19.847
so where's your uncle now?

02:20.056 --> 02:22.224
At a conference in Cornwall.

02:22.475 --> 02:23.433
"Life in the slow lane."

03:03.808 --> 03:07.519
Whoops-a-daisy! That's the way to do it.

03:08.646 --> 03:09.354
What a pity!

03:23.411 --> 03:27.122
I wish I knew more about my uncle,
but he's not an easy man to pin down.

03:27.957 --> 03:28.665
What the...?!

03:42.889 --> 03:43.889
And that's about it.

03:44.807 --> 03:45.682
The end.

03:46.935 --> 03:47.726
Thank you, Alex.

03:50.855 --> 03:53.565
- Okay, so, if you come round about...
- I really wanna come.

03:53.733 --> 03:54.566
Hey, Sabina.

03:55.568 --> 03:56.526
Alex!

03:56.819 --> 03:58.820
do you wanna do something
this weekend?

04:00.448 --> 04:04.576
I can't, I've riding lessons and
I'm going out with my parents.

04:04.994 --> 04:05.953
It doesn't matter.

04:06.829 --> 04:08.622
Maybe next weekend?

04:09.707 --> 04:10.582
Whatever.

04:15.088 --> 04:16.338
Hey, are you coming home?

04:16.714 --> 04:17.964
Yeah, I'm on my way now.

04:18.966 --> 04:20.091
How was the conference?

04:20.969 --> 04:21.969
It was fine.

04:22.720 --> 04:25.597
- You know how they are.
- No, I don't. You never tell me.

04:26.349 --> 04:28.058
There isn't much to tell. Wait a minute.

04:31.354 --> 04:32.604
Hello? Hello?

04:33.022 --> 04:33.981
Hello?

04:36.484 --> 04:37.776
- What was that?
- Nothing.

04:37.986 --> 04:43.156
I'm sorry I wasn't there last week,
but, this trip came out of nowhere.

04:43.366 --> 04:44.074
As always.

04:45.868 --> 04:50.330
I'll be back in time for dinner, and
then we've got the whole weekend.

04:50.498 --> 04:52.666
- Really?
- When did I ever let you down?

04:52.875 --> 04:54.126
Do you really want me to answer that?

04:55.920 --> 04:58.005
I know. Look, I'll see you soon, okay?

04:58.464 --> 04:59.381
I'm glad you called.

05:00.675 --> 05:01.508
Yeah, me too.

05:03.052 --> 05:04.011
I'll see you later,

05:04.387 --> 05:05.512
Bye.

05:09.017 --> 05:13.061
And then I see you again

05:13.688 --> 05:16.815
And that look is in your eyes

05:16.983 --> 05:21.403
You blew my mind but it wasn't real

05:48.556 --> 05:50.057
You and I

05:51.059 --> 05:56.021
We're floating in a kaleidoscope of lies

05:58.941 --> 06:01.568
Tell me why

06:02.820 --> 06:08.200
You dress the truth in a velvet disguise

06:10.078 --> 06:13.872
I wanna break free

06:15.291 --> 06:18.960
You can never shake what I believe

06:23.299 --> 06:28.220
And the sunrise paints
the skies red in shame

06:29.597 --> 06:36.395
And you wake up to find the whole
world's gone insane

06:36.562 --> 06:40.565
But if you hide yourself away Well I say

06:40.775 --> 06:45.904
Hey, you've only got yourself to blame

06:50.618 --> 06:52.285
Gotta decide

06:54.080 --> 06:59.418
Whether or not you believe all those lies.

07:01.462 --> 07:05.132
But take it from me

07:06.467 --> 07:11.304
They've got a strangle hold on
the air we breathe

07:14.892 --> 07:19.521
And the sunrise burns
the sky red in shame.

07:20.898 --> 07:27.237
And you wake up to find the whole
world's gone insane

07:27.530 --> 07:31.450
But if you hide yourself away
Well I say

07:34.245 --> 07:46.548
Jack?

07:50.511 --> 07:51.636
Jack, are you here?

08:04.775 --> 08:05.567
Oh, Jack.

08:07.820 --> 08:09.571
Good day at school?

08:10.281 --> 08:11.948
Why are we speaking Japanese?

08:12.241 --> 08:14.993
We're having a special dinner.

08:15.369 --> 08:16.411
sushi.

08:22.210 --> 08:23.376
Arigatou.

08:24.086 --> 08:24.961
Let's begin.

08:28.758 --> 08:33.135
I met the most amazing guy
at the fish market today.

08:33.763 --> 08:35.514
Do you know what the problem with
this country is?

08:35.806 --> 08:38.558
Every good-looking guy is either
gay or married.

08:38.851 --> 08:40.309
Except for you, but you're too young.

08:43.606 --> 08:44.814
Will you please eat something?

08:45.900 --> 08:48.318
He's coming. He's just stuck in traffic.

08:48.569 --> 08:49.694
He would have rung.

08:50.321 --> 08:52.739
He's probably gone to the office
and the next thing we know,

08:53.032 --> 08:54.407
he's going to Hong Kong.

08:55.159 --> 08:56.284
Let me down again.

08:57.745 --> 09:00.789
- You know his work means a lot to him.
- Yeah, it means a lot.

09:02.041 --> 09:03.833
All the more for us.

09:05.586 --> 09:07.546
What did I tell you? Who's a genius?

09:54.176 --> 09:54.968
Come on.

10:06.689 --> 10:08.607
We are gathered here today...

10:08.983 --> 10:12.611
to bid farewell to a man called

10:13.404 --> 10:16.281
A reminder that even in the midst of life...

10:16.741 --> 10:19.367
we are all of us walking together...

10:20.202 --> 10:21.911
in the shadow of death.

10:22.246 --> 10:24.664
Ian Rider was a good man.

10:25.249 --> 10:28.543
Everyone who worked with him will
remember him for his courage...

10:29.253 --> 10:30.503
and his loyalty.

10:31.380 --> 10:35.759
He was, above all, a true patriot.

10:36.010 --> 10:38.511
We have entrusted our brother
to God's mercy...

10:39.013 --> 10:41.806
and we now commit his body
to the ground.

10:43.726 --> 10:45.018
Earth to earth.

10:45.227 --> 10:47.145
Ashes to ashes.

10:47.730 --> 10:49.522
Dust to dust.

10:49.774 --> 10:53.234
Ian Rider, a true patriot.

10:53.527 --> 10:55.779
True patriot.

11:12.421 --> 11:15.340
To Him, be glory forever.

11:16.050 --> 11:17.008
Amen.

11:31.357 --> 11:34.067
I'm John Crawford from
the Royal and General Bank.

11:34.276 --> 11:36.569
I just want you to know,
you have our condolences.

11:37.446 --> 11:41.741
It's a tragedy. A car crash.
If only he had been wearing a seatbelt.

11:42.576 --> 11:43.368
Thank you.

11:43.577 --> 11:47.080
This is Alan Blunt.
He's the Chairman of the Bank.

11:47.498 --> 11:48.456
Alex.

11:48.874 --> 11:53.211
sorry about your uncle.
We're going to miss him.

11:53.754 --> 11:55.922
- He talked a lot about you.
- That's strange.

11:56.465 --> 11:58.174
Because he never mentioned you.

12:01.095 --> 12:04.931
his is my deputy, Mrs Jones.

12:06.058 --> 12:08.351
I'll be in contact very soon, Alex.

12:09.061 --> 12:09.894
Why?

12:10.354 --> 12:14.524
After what's happened, the question
of who's going to look after you.

12:14.734 --> 12:17.068
- I'll look after him.
- We're just trying to help.

12:20.489 --> 12:24.367
I'm sure we'll meet again,
Hopefully, somewhere a little less

12:25.327 --> 12:26.244
gloomy.

12:27.913 --> 12:30.373
My uncle always wore a seatbelt,
Mr Blunt.

12:33.419 --> 12:37.922
- He was a very careful man.
- Not careful enough.

12:42.011 --> 12:44.012
Did you mean what you said about
looking after me?

12:44.513 --> 12:46.264
Of course I did, idiot.

12:47.141 --> 12:48.975
You know I would never leave you.
Yeah.

12:49.143 --> 12:50.643
Besides, who else is there?

12:51.145 --> 12:54.689
I mean, will you be allowed to?
We are not even related.

12:54.940 --> 12:58.568
how much more related
do you wanna be?

12:59.028 --> 13:01.529
Is it just me,
or were those bankers weird?

13:06.368 --> 13:08.661
I've been doing this all day!

13:09.038 --> 13:10.288
What the heck are you doing?!

13:11.373 --> 13:12.415
Alex?

13:15.044 --> 13:17.879
Alex!

13:59.421 --> 14:00.380
Idiot!

14:05.344 --> 14:06.261
Get out of it!

14:19.775 --> 14:20.859
What are you playing at?!

14:39.962 --> 14:43.756
I predict a riot

14:54.393 --> 14:56.519
If you see that Nigel,
you tell him I want him, all right?

15:25.382 --> 15:27.800
What's going on?!

15:29.511 --> 15:33.222
The Rider car should have been done
two days ago! so do it now, all right?!

15:33.432 --> 15:35.975
- I didn't get the paperwork!
- Just do it, Harry!

15:37.227 --> 15:41.064
- I'm going to Liverpool street.
- Liverpool street? What, the station?

15:42.524 --> 15:46.027
Yes, you berk! Where else?
I'm gonna take them the stuff.

15:47.988 --> 15:49.614
Bryce? Bryce?

16:04.213 --> 16:05.171
Tyson, get down!

16:08.008 --> 16:08.758
What?

17:15.534 --> 17:16.159
Harry!

17:29.840 --> 17:30.840
Come here!

17:31.133 --> 17:31.966
There he goes!

18:31.026 --> 18:31.859
Close in.

18:32.653 --> 18:34.779
How did he get in?
Get out the way!

18:43.664 --> 18:46.666
sure they said they were coming here?
They could have gone have gone anywhere.

18:46.917 --> 18:50.128
They're not taking the train,
they're bringing stuff to the station.

18:50.420 --> 18:52.421
- Where? - I don't know.

18:56.260 --> 18:57.510
- Jack. - What?

18:58.387 --> 18:59.345
Over there.

19:01.515 --> 19:03.182
It's that guy from the funeral.

19:03.684 --> 19:06.310
What's his name?

19:07.396 --> 19:08.354
Alex?

19:20.450 --> 19:24.412
The stormbreaker. Coming soon from
Sayle Enterprises.

19:25.414 --> 19:26.080
- Look out. - sorry.

19:45.058 --> 19:48.936
The stormbreaker.
Coming soon from Sayle Enterprises.

20:57.547 --> 20:59.215
Welcome to Arrivals.

20:59.591 --> 21:03.511
Please remain seated and
await docking procedure.

21:12.980 --> 21:13.938
Good morning.

21:20.070 --> 21:22.863
Good morning,
Alex. shouldn't you be at school?

21:24.283 --> 21:26.158
I was at Liverpool street station.

21:27.369 --> 21:28.577
And now I'm here.

21:29.288 --> 21:30.246
That's right.

21:35.002 --> 21:36.002
Morning.

21:38.964 --> 21:41.465
so what is this place? Hogwarts?

21:42.175 --> 21:45.428
I think you've probably realised,
your uncle didn't work for a bank.

21:45.595 --> 21:48.514
The Royal and General doesn't exist.
He worked for us.

21:48.849 --> 21:49.807
Who are you?

21:50.434 --> 21:54.854
My name is Mrs Jones. I run the
special Operation Division of M16.

21:55.439 --> 21:57.106
Wait a minute,
are you saying he lied to me?

21:57.316 --> 22:00.359
He lied to everyone.
sorry. Part of his job.

22:04.031 --> 22:07.241
Ian Rider was one of our best agents.
Until you got him killed.

22:07.451 --> 22:11.620
He got himself killed.
It's an occupational hazard, I'm afraid.

22:11.997 --> 22:15.958
- Not if you're a banker.
- Mr Blunt wants to talk to you.

22:16.293 --> 22:18.878
We have a proposition
we'd like to make.

22:29.681 --> 22:31.557
We want you to work for us.

22:34.478 --> 22:38.064
- You're not being serious?
- It's not my habit to make jokes

22:38.565 --> 22:39.774
Well, you're making one now.

22:41.193 --> 22:44.195
I don't wanna be a spy. In case
you haven't noticed, I'm still at school.

22:44.613 --> 22:46.280
I'll take that as a 'no', then.

22:46.531 --> 22:48.741
What a great shame.

22:50.035 --> 22:52.578
Your uncle would be very disappointed.

22:52.913 --> 22:54.663
- What? - Letting him down like that.

22:54.915 --> 22:58.250
But then, I suppose, young people...

22:58.502 --> 22:59.919
How can you say that?

23:00.212 --> 23:04.048
He wouldn't want me here. He spent his
life making sure I didn't know about this.

23:04.257 --> 23:05.257
Really?

23:06.051 --> 23:08.677
Then how do you explain ...

23:10.764 --> 23:11.597
this?

23:16.103 --> 23:17.937
First-rate martial arts moves.

23:18.105 --> 23:20.564
Perfectly executed. Who trained you?

23:20.774 --> 23:24.443
- Nobody trained me.
- You're a black belt at karate.

23:25.153 --> 23:27.029
Who paid for the lessons?

23:27.280 --> 23:28.948
- It was my choice. - No!

23:31.118 --> 23:33.911
All your life, Ian Rider was preparing you.

23:34.121 --> 23:37.915
You speak French,
German and Japanese.

23:38.208 --> 23:42.503
He took me on holiday. You've been
scuba diving, mountain climbing ...

23:42.754 --> 23:45.881
abseiling, white water rafting
They were my hobbies.

23:46.133 --> 23:48.509
rifle shooting, martial arts.

23:51.179 --> 23:52.763
He was training you.

23:53.598 --> 23:57.059
That's not how it was.
You're trying to spoil everything.

23:58.645 --> 24:01.230
Please put me back in the photo booth
and show me the way out.

24:03.191 --> 24:05.151
I'm surprised, really.

24:05.485 --> 24:09.155
I thought you'd want to
get back at your uncle's killers.

24:11.408 --> 24:17.121
How's that housekeeper of yours?
What's her name? Jack Starbright.

24:17.330 --> 24:19.707
I suppose she'll have started
packing by now.

24:20.333 --> 24:23.043
- Why? What do you mean?
- Didn't she tell you?

24:23.253 --> 24:27.298
Her visa ran out seven years ago.
she'll be deported any day now.

24:28.467 --> 24:31.343
Actually, we might prosecute her first.

24:32.345 --> 24:33.512
Make an example.

24:34.473 --> 24:37.475
Working here illegally,
may mean a prison sentence.

24:38.685 --> 24:39.768
What are you?

24:41.188 --> 24:42.897
What kind of people are you?

24:43.899 --> 24:47.485
Ones that normally get their way.

24:47.861 --> 24:51.322
Liverpool street concourse now ready
for departure.

25:09.049 --> 25:10.132
stop flaking at the back.
Get a move on!

25:10.467 --> 25:11.634
Get up there!

25:11.927 --> 25:12.718
Get moving!

25:12.886 --> 25:15.513
Come on then, lad, look lively.

25:19.518 --> 25:20.559
On your feet.

25:21.561 --> 25:24.730
Gentlemen, this is our latest recruit.

25:24.940 --> 25:27.566
He's here for two weeks' training.

25:27.943 --> 25:31.111
Don't ask me about it,
because I don't know a thing.

25:31.321 --> 25:33.072
Ijust do as I'm told.

25:33.907 --> 25:37.743
We have no names here.
We have no ranks.

25:38.245 --> 25:44.208
This is 'K' Unit. Fox, Bear,
Eagle and Wolf.

25:45.252 --> 25:47.378
You'll be Cub. Get him a bed.

25:53.802 --> 25:57.346
- What the heck is this?
- It's a kid.

25:58.515 --> 26:02.017
Who the heck do you think you are?
A schoolboy?

26:02.561 --> 26:03.811
They've gotta be joking.

26:05.855 --> 26:06.897
what's your name?

26:07.732 --> 26:08.941
Who sent you here?!

26:09.568 --> 26:10.442
I can't tell you.

26:11.611 --> 26:12.611
He can't tell me.

26:13.405 --> 26:16.407
Course you can.
You must be with special Operations.

26:16.616 --> 26:18.784
They're the only ones stupid enough
to come up with something like this.

26:18.994 --> 26:19.660
I said...

26:24.833 --> 26:25.916
I can't tell you.

26:26.501 --> 26:29.420
That's very good. someone been
teaching you self-defense?

26:30.880 --> 26:32.298
Ain't gonna help you here.

26:33.258 --> 26:35.634
No pain, no gain. Move it!

26:35.844 --> 26:37.177
You ain't gonna last two days.

26:41.516 --> 26:42.891
Get a move on, schoolboy!

26:44.686 --> 26:46.270
Keep moving, Cub!

26:50.108 --> 26:53.652
DAY 4
Get up, you! stay with it.

26:59.492 --> 27:03.996
DAY 7 That's it, one in front
of the other. Hurry up.

27:04.956 --> 27:06.999
Come on, get up!

27:07.334 --> 27:10.836
Move it, Cub! Come on!

27:11.504 --> 27:13.130
DAY 9 Come on!

27:13.506 --> 27:15.883
Come on, go! Go on, go, go, go!

27:17.177 --> 27:18.469
That's it, Cub, go on.

27:20.013 --> 27:22.348
And all I wanna hear
is the message beep

27:24.768 --> 27:25.351
And stop.

27:27.687 --> 27:30.689
Look at him. Come on, Cub.

27:31.691 --> 27:34.818
You're not in the playground now,
Cub. Move it!

27:35.904 --> 27:37.279
Come on, hurry up.

27:39.699 --> 27:40.658
Idiot!

27:41.618 --> 27:44.453
Love forever, love is free

27:44.663 --> 27:48.040
Let's turn forever, you and me

27:48.208 --> 27:50.959
Windmill, windmill for the land

27:51.294 --> 27:56.173
Is everybody in?

28:11.189 --> 28:13.607
'K' Unit, stand fast.

28:13.983 --> 28:16.735
You have failed the exercise.

28:17.737 --> 28:18.153
What an idiot.

28:18.321 --> 28:21.240
Well, well, well. What have we got here?

28:22.117 --> 28:23.450
You idiot, Wolf.

28:27.539 --> 28:28.372
We're finished!

28:28.581 --> 28:31.083
We've blown the whole exercise.
We'll get kicked out!

28:32.252 --> 28:34.294
This is your fault. You had the map.

28:36.339 --> 28:38.257
Never listens. He's always gotta be right.

28:38.508 --> 28:41.885
Who puts a light on in the middle of
an exercise? Unbelievable.

28:44.931 --> 28:47.349
- There's a fireplace.
- How did you know?

28:47.684 --> 28:50.352
- I saw the chimney on the way in.
- The kid's right.

28:51.062 --> 28:52.104
It's clear.

28:52.439 --> 28:55.733
You think they would leave it open
if they thought we could all climb up?

28:55.942 --> 28:57.234
You can't, you're too big.

28:58.570 --> 28:59.570
But I can.

29:01.281 --> 29:02.906
Go on then, Cub, up you go.

29:21.801 --> 29:23.594
All right, mate? Cup of tea?

29:23.803 --> 29:25.179
Oh, yeah, thanks.

29:25.722 --> 29:29.141
- We should take that lot back to base.
- No, later'll be fine.

29:29.976 --> 29:30.726
see ya.

29:31.728 --> 29:33.520
Fancy a nice cup of tea, boys?

29:33.772 --> 29:35.606
shut up, sit down.

30:05.470 --> 30:07.012
What's that lot playing at,
having a kid with them?

30:07.305 --> 30:10.516
Dunno. He looks like a schoolboy.
He can only be about 14.

30:10.809 --> 30:12.601
That's a bit young for
special Forces, isn't it?

30:12.936 --> 30:15.145
We'd better get him back to his mummy.

30:15.355 --> 30:17.481
Yeah, he probably needs a nappy change.

30:17.982 --> 30:20.609
Must be his bedtime. Time for his hot milk.

30:21.277 --> 30:22.945
Boss? Are we moving?

30:23.613 --> 30:25.322
Hold on, lad!

30:25.532 --> 30:28.826
- Hold on, fellas! - Jump out!

30:41.881 --> 30:44.675
Cuts. Bruises. Fractured limbs.

30:45.260 --> 30:46.969
It's a miracle no-one was killed.

30:47.178 --> 30:51.473
I'm very sorry, Major.
We will be talking to our man -- Boy.

30:51.850 --> 30:53.976
He's no child, Mr Blunt.

30:55.478 --> 30:56.854
He's a lethal weapon.

31:01.067 --> 31:02.234
He's ready.

31:20.670 --> 31:21.962
Heard you were leaving.

31:23.965 --> 31:25.048
Yeah, that's right.

31:26.759 --> 31:28.051
What you did earlier...

31:29.596 --> 31:31.013
if it weren't for you...

31:35.977 --> 31:36.894
Here you are.

31:55.914 --> 31:59.124
And finally, an amazing gift made to
the British nation.

31:59.334 --> 32:04.421
The stormbreaker is the most
sophisticated PC of the 21st century...

32:04.631 --> 32:08.342
and one month ago, its multi-
billionaire inventor, Darrius sayle...

32:08.551 --> 32:10.594
made his astonishing announcement.

32:10.887 --> 32:14.598
I'm gonna give a stormbreaker to
every school in the country.

32:16.309 --> 32:19.978
